&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team/role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Senior Data Analyst to join our Support Product Squad. This role will work closely with the Product, Design, Ops and Engineering teams that are focused on creating a global chatbot led conversational support strategy. This is a very dynamic role in which one day you will find yourself running workshops, defining data requirements and scoping requirements to meet product strategy; another day you might be conducting research, data analysis or transcript reviews.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Converting raw conversational and customer support data into insights that will lead to informed business decisions and high quality product backlog.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creating, developing, and applying machine learning approaches to conversational decision making and dialogue management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpreting data and analysing results using statistical techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting analysis of operational and conversational data to provide insight into current processes, agent behaviour and automation opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing knowledge graphs to represent customer support topics and improving service scope of chatbots and efficacy of FAQ and self-support content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analysing large scale conversational datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being comfortable in applying analysis results to multiple global languages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using expert knowledge of state-of-the-art methods and tools to consistently find the most effective, efficient, stable, explainable, and elegant approaches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use and present research findings in ways that inform and sometimes guide business and product strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A mathematical ability to analyse, model and interpret data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years research and/or work experience with Natural Language Processing (either text or voice)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of NLU (natural language understanding) and NLG (Natural Language Generation) technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proven problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using open source data, functions and libraries for data science and machine learning is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of creating and maintaining labelled dataset out of unstructured conversational transcripts is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills and ability to tell product stories using data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Written and spoken proficiency in multiply languages is a plus with an added advantage if proficient in Mandarin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
